1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,839
So basically, Before I show the answer, pause and try to guess.

2
00:00:05,789 --> 00:00:14,105
But here's where it gets really interesting,  "How do you ensure global ordering of all messages in a topic?

3
00:00:14,105 --> 00:00:17,197
Set the topic to 1 partition.

4
00:00:17,197 --> 00:00:22,197
This is the only way to achieve global ordering in Kafka.

5
00:00:22,197 --> 00:00:29,302
The trade-off is zero parallelism: only one consumer can process the topic at a time.

6
00:00:29,302 --> 00:00:36,434
Global ordering + high throughput are fundamentally in tension in Kafka's architecture.

7
00:00:36,434 --> 00:00:43,092
Real talk: I've seen senior engineers at Uber get this wrong in interviews.

8
00:00:43,092 --> 00:00:45,486
Don't be that person.

